daysant license

Revision 3
1. Definitions

    “This license” refers to the daysant license as at its latest revision.
    “Copyright” refers to any laws or provisions that relate to copyright or are copyright-like.
    “You” refers to any party who is a licensee. You may either be an individual or an organization.
    The “author” refers to any party who holds copyright on the work. This includes the original creator and all other contributors.
    The “work” refers to the copyrightable work licensed under this license.
    The “source” refers to the form of the work used to create and modify the work.
    The “product” refers all forms of the work that is not the source.
    To “use” a work means to do anything with the work that, without the grants and permissions of this license, would make you liable for copyright infringement.
    To “modify” a work means to adapt or copy a work, in whole or in part, other than the creation of a verbatim copy.
        The resulting work is the “modified work” based off the earlier work called the “original work”.
    To “distribute” a work means to use the work which makes the product available to any third party. The work can be a modified work or the original work.
    An “attribution method” refers to any one of a hyperlink, button, menu option, or any other mechanism by which parties who use the work can find information that is specified in later provisions.

2. Agreement to this license

    By using, modifying, distributing, or copying this work, you agree to this license in full.
    In the event you take part in any action that contradicts or violates the provisions of this license, it immediately becomes void and you may be liable for copyright infringement.

