            The International Labour Organization;
            The General Data Protection Regulation.
        Any purposes that involve offensive applications;
            Defensive applications involve the use of force or violence to actively protect against ongoing attacks to protect life, property, territory. This license does not recognize pre-emptive force to prevent a perceived threat’s actions as legitimate defense.
            Offensive applications involve the use of force or violence in any way that is not solely for the purpose of defense against an ongoing attack. This includes, but is not limited to, pre-emptive strikes, aggression, or any use of force intended to cause harm, damage, or destruction outside of immediate self-defense.
